# 📱 Flutter Project Structure for Whisky Hikes

## Project Overview

The Whisky Hikes Flutter app follows a clean architecture pattern with clear separation of concerns between UI, business logic, and data layers.

## Directory Structure

```
lib/
├── main.dart                    # App entry point
├── config/                      # Configuration and setup
│   ├── dependencies.dart        # Dependency injection
│   ├── l10n/                    # Localization files
│   └── routing/                 # Navigation configuration
├── UI/                          # User interface components
│   ├── auth/                    # Authentication screens
│   ├── checkout/                # Checkout flow
│   ├── core/                    # Shared UI components
│   ├── home/                    # Home screen and widgets
│   ├── payment/                 # Payment screens
│   └── profile/                 # User profile screens
├── data/                        # Data layer
│   ├── repositories/            # Data access layer
│   └── services/                # External service integrations
└── domain/                      # Business logic layer
    └── models/                  # Data models and entities
```

## Architecture Layers

### UI Layer ([lib/UI/](mdc:lib/UI/))
- **Screens**: Full-page UI components
- **Widgets**: Reusable UI components
- **ViewModels**: State management for UI components
- **Navigation**: Screen routing and transitions

### Data Layer ([lib/data/](mdc:lib/data/))
- **Repositories**: Abstract data access interfaces
- **Services**: External API integrations (Supabase, Stripe)
- **Local Storage**: Caching and offline data

### Domain Layer ([lib/domain/](mdc:lib/domain/))
- **Models**: Business entities and data structures
- **Use Cases**: Business logic and rules
- **Interfaces**: Abstract contracts for data access

## Key Components

### Authentication System
- [auth_service.dart](mdc:lib/data/services/auth/auth_service.dart) - Supabase authentication
- [user_repository.dart](mdc:lib/data/repositories/user_repository.dart) - User data management
- [login_page.dart](mdc:lib/UI/auth/login_page.dart) - Login UI

### Payment Integration
- [stripe_service.dart](mdc:lib/data/services/payment/stripe_service.dart) - Stripe payment processing
- [payment_repository.dart](mdc:lib/data/repositories/payment_repository.dart) - Payment data management
- [checkout_page.dart](mdc:lib/UI/checkout/checkout_page.dart) - Checkout flow

### Navigation
- [router.dart](mdc:lib/config/routing/router.dart) - App navigation configuration
- [routes.dart](mdc:lib/config/routing/routes.dart) - Route definitions

### Data Models
- [order.dart](mdc:lib/domain/models/order.dart) - Order management
- [payment_intent.dart](mdc:lib/domain/models/payment_intent.dart) - Payment processing
- [hike.dart](mdc:lib/domain/models/hike.dart) - Hike data structure

## Configuration

### Dependencies
- [dependencies.dart](mdc:lib/config/dependencies.dart) - Service locator and dependency injection
- [pubspec.yaml](mdc:pubspec.yaml) - Package dependencies and app metadata

### Localization
- [l10n.yaml](mdc:l10n.yaml) - Localization configuration
- [lib/config/l10n/](mdc:lib/config/l10n/) - Translation files

## Testing Structure

```
test/
├── config/                      # Test configuration
├── data/                        # Data layer tests
├── domain/                      # Domain layer tests
├── UI/                          # UI component tests
├── integration/                 # End-to-end tests
├── mocks/                       # Mock objects
└── run_all_tests.dart          # Test runner
```

## Development Workflow

### Adding New Features
1. Create models in [lib/domain/models/](mdc:lib/domain/models/)
2. Implement repositories in [lib/data/repositories/](mdc:lib/data/repositories/)
3. Create services in [lib/data/services/](mdc:lib/data/services/)
4. Build UI components in [lib/UI/](mdc:lib/UI/)
5. Add tests in corresponding [test/](mdc:test/) directories

### State Management
- Use ViewModels for screen state management
- Implement reactive patterns with Streams
- Keep business logic in domain layer
- UI components should be stateless when possible

### Error Handling
- Implement consistent error handling patterns
- Use Result types for operations that can fail
- Provide user-friendly error messages
- Log errors for debugging

## Integration Points

### Supabase Backend
- Authentication via [auth_service.dart](mdc:lib/data/services/auth/auth_service.dart)
- Database operations via [backend_api.dart](mdc:lib/data/services/database/backend_api.dart)
- Real-time subscriptions for live updates

### Payment Processing
- Stripe integration via [stripe_service.dart](mdc:lib/data/services/payment/stripe_service.dart)
- Order management through [payment_repository.dart](mdc:lib/data/repositories/payment_repository.dart)
- Secure payment flow in [checkout_page.dart](mdc:lib/UI/checkout/checkout_page.dart)

## Performance Considerations

- Use lazy loading for images and heavy content
- Implement efficient caching strategies
- Minimize widget rebuilds with proper state management
- Use const constructors where possible
- Implement pagination for large data sets

## Security Features

- Secure API communication with Supabase
- Token-based authentication
- Secure payment processing with Stripe
- Input validation and sanitization
- Secure local storage for sensitive data
